This paper proposes a method for holding a dictionary data structure in the spirit of Bloom Filters, which is a well-known data structure in computer science used for membership queries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves solving equations in GF(2^k), which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses hash functions, which is a topic in both data structures and cryptography. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Cryptography and Security) are also likely categories.
